subtitle: Welcome back everyone to Astral Doorway, this is Gene, on this episode; I'll be sharing quite
a special experience that i had recently you may recall in the first episode i talked about
teaching a class in the astral, well in this experience that i'm going to share i
attended one, now i suspect that astral classes in general, are more common than we realize and
that almost everyone unconsciously attends these classes in their sleep, now that's just
a speculation of course but for me it's something that i've noticed is a common theme in the astral
kendra kay asked uh "how does this happen? how do people get to these classes unconsciously?" well my
honest answer is i don't know but i suspect there are beings or people who devote themselves to
helping humanity and that they're responsible for organizing these classes and bringing people there
for the purpose of humanity's spiritual growth; even if those people don't remember the
experiences you know there does seem to be some sort of subconscious learning going on in these
classes which surely affects people's conscious minds in some way, now when i taught that class
that i mentioned in the first video i didn't know how it happened, i didn't organize it, i was just
in front of a room with a lot of people and i was looking into this classroom and i just knew
that this is what i had to do i had to go in and teach these people and i gave a lesson on astral
projection; i didn't question it i just completely went with it, as if a part of me had already agreed
to it, so yeah, now in this experience i'm going to share i walked into a class in the middle of the
lesson and as far as i was aware i was the only conscious participant there, apart from the teacher
of course, so this happened in the very early hours of the morning i had a series of dreams beforehand
and another astral projection which involved me shapeshifting into a cat for the first time...
after that i returned to my physical body and then i proceeded to get back up out of my physical body
and i proceeded to leave my apartment here in london, i enjoyed a peaceful stroll on the streets
of london for a bit in the astral i live quite near the city center so it's always interesting
to see what's going on around here, everything was exactly the same as it was in the physical, at one
point i did start to lose awareness as i said i already had other experiences before this
so perhaps i was losing stamina a bit, so i sat down cross-legged on the pavement
and i meditated; i got into a zen-like state and focused on the rustling of the trees nearby, looked
at the blue sky, and just appreciated where i was, i got some weird looks from people passing by
but at this point my awareness was coming back uh you know you could say the experience was becoming
hyper realistic when it just feels more real than the physical when you feel the sun in your skin
and you look at the details of a wall or a fence or the pavement i was looking at, experiences can
become super real like this i wish i was an artist and i could articulate how real the experience
was and how experiences like this in the astral can be, i got back up and i carried on walking
on the familiar streets that i always walk on in the physical there weren't many surprises
because everything was identical, however, i then noticed as i came across this familiar street
something very different; in the physical there's this roundabout in the middle of a busy street
which has some grass and trees and benches on it, it's like a mini park with cars that are
always driving around it, now in the astral in this experience instead of seeing that usual roundabout
i saw this huge white majestic church / temple it was beautiful immaculate and tall, now opposite
this roundabout there's usually a christian church so i looked over at that thinking maybe it's just
the same church but transformed and in the wrong location but nope that regular church was still
there and frankly it looked meek in comparison to this magnificent temple, so i was a little confused
and curious i just had to go inside so i crossed the road and walked up these many steps to get to
this huge wooden doorway, an astral doorway so to speak excuse the pun, now i opened the door
and i was a little surprised to see there was a sort of sermon going on, a mass, at least i
thought it was filled with around 100 people sat inside, now personally being raised catholic,
and someone who enjoys Gnostic teachings you know i'm open to all religions so i didn't mind joining
i'll be honest i just expected this to be a regular christian or catholic mass or something
so i went inside and sat down on the back row next to this indian fellow who gave me a polite nod,
even though the temple was majestic on the outside it was surprisingly quite basic and
humble on the inside it had massive pillars on either row with the usual long wooden benches
you see in most churches with the stage at the end and on the stage was a woman... now i'll call
her the priestess, which is fitting since this was taking place in a temple and she was leading this
sort of class she was sitting down behind a standard school looking desk on a very basic chair
now what really caught my attention and piqued my interest was that she was wearing a robe which was
white and silver, now something i've not shared yet is that i used to be part of a Gnostic group
for some years where we learned about various esoteric things and one of those things that my
teacher at the time revealed to me was that it's common for spiritual masters in the astral plane
to wear silver and white robes and that that's one way you can identify whether a teacher is of pure
and good intention, uh and similarly just to let you all know if you see someone wearing
black and red robes then they're supposed to usually be from a darker background and
they probably practice things which are of a more negative nature, so as i looked at her
we made eye contact even though i was at the back of the building telepathically she welcomed
me and said hello and she recognized me as being conscious compared to everyone else in the church
now this sort of communication in the astral is a sort of norm over there it's not
unusual to communicate information to others in this way, so yeah i liked this priestess
she seemed powerful and wise i had an immediate sense of admiration for her she smiled
at me i smiled back and she kindly communicated that this was a sort of basic public teaching and
that everyone here was asleep; asleep in the sense that their consciousness was asleep, she basically
said that i didn't really need to be there but i was welcome, of course i wanted to stay i was very
interested in how all of this worked i was very curious uh you know the idea of people leaving
the body unconsciously at night has been playing on my mind for a while so this was the perfect
opportunity to observe what people are like in these states, i also noticed that while me
and the priestess were looking at each other and communicating telepathically i could tell
that at the same time she was still talking to other people as if she were multitasking on some
level that's incomprehensible to me to be honest so she was clearly a skilled being
i'm reminded of hindu gods who are depicted with many heads because that is basically what i saw i
like the picture you can see on the screen, so i tried to pay attention to what she was teaching
i heard people asking questions about god and the priestess quoting verses from the
quran and the bible but i was more interested in the people, everyone looked should i say
too happy it was almost a bit creepy actually like they were overly fascinated with the class
it was strange, a strange energy, it's like when people get too immersed with a tv show and they
forget themselves, and as i was looking at everyone a group of about five people from the middle row
were looking at me smiling and invited me to sit next to them, a part of me recognized them but i
didn't really know who they were on the level of my usual physical mind they clearly knew
who i was though so i was a little confused but i just got up anyway and sat next to them they were
super friendly smiley and welcoming there was a real sense of friendship and that i knew them it
was nice but a little strange too but i just carried on anyway, perhaps i've unconsciously
attended classes with these people before who knows anyway, after the priestess had finished
speaking for some time she came down from the stage and she proceeded to ask everyone to get out
their masks which they must have made towards the beginning of the class now i looked on and wonder
at everyone getting out these wooden masks as if the priestess had made them do an arts
and craft lesson beforehand they were really interesting to look at each one was different
now i tried to look online for what these looked the closest to and i found that they
look very similar to these old shamanic masks which you can see on the screen
it was fairly clear to me that the priestess was doing a lesson on the ego that's my guess anyway
you can take your own guess at what i'm going to describe... for me the mask was symbolic for what
kind of ego or facade we all live behind, so yeah as everyone was taking out their masks they were
showing each other they were very excited very proud of what they had made i felt a little left
out because i was empty-handed and didn't have one to show off but it was fine i was happy watching
now once the priestess had everyone's attention again she began one by one taking someone's mask
inspected it and then used what i'll describe as a magic pen which she simply tapped on the mask
and the mask would slowly turn into gold, turning it from this rugged imperfect wooden mask
to a perfectly splendorous and shining golden mask, she did this to everyone's mask one by one, when
she got to one woman this woman became distressed and was almost crying saying "i don't want my mask
turning into gold, please!" but the priestess just calmly took it from her anyway and she said in
a profound and slow way whilst looking into her eyes... "this is necessary" and she turned her mask
into gold and the woman took the mask back just silent and staring at her new and improved mask
now at this point the previously excited atmosphere had mysteriously shifted and
there was a silence as everyone looked on in awe at what the priestess was doing
there seemed to be a shift in consciousness and i sensed that there was definitely some kind of
subconscious learning that was taking place, as the priestess continued to each person eventually she
came to me i felt a bit awkward because i didn't have a mask but instead she approached me and
smiled and gently held up my wrist revealing a bracelet with a crucifix pendant on it and
she turned the pendant into gold, i was quite surprised and she just smiled i said thank you
i didn't really know what to make of it to be honest i was in awe like everyone else
i don't exactly know what was meant by the gold it sounds as if the teaching was to imply
that we must work on or perfect our egos, our masks that we live behind
we have to polish or improve our personality, or psychological state, that's my guess
you know because for me when i first started working on my ego and meditation you know the
ego isn't something that you can just uh get rid of or destroy immediately you have to start by
developing certain good habits being polite being good to others so that you start having a better
sense of self etc, so yeah that's my guess at the teaching and i suspect that there are deeper
symbolisms so if any of you have an interpretation of what this symbolic teaching meant i'd be
very grateful to have your insights too so please do comment below if you have any ideas
now what happened next i suspect happened differently for everyone else in the room
the priestess went back to the stage and she began to shapeshift
everyone must have seen a different thing because what i saw was quite personal to me
when i was younger maybe around eight years old i had an extremely vivid dream or nightmare should
i call it that has always stayed in the back of my mind my entire life, so in the dream as a child
i opened my bedroom door and a huge fat samurai in full black armor with a mask was stood there
it had this menacing and powerful presence, it gave me such a fright as a child and i ran from it
it didn't matter how far i ran every time i turned around to check if i lost it it was still there my
entire life i always wondered if it was a positive or negative being because even though i was scared
as a child it was actually quite a calm being which actually never attacked me or threatened
me in any way so here i am 20 years later in the astral watching on in awe at this priestess
turning into this huge samurai being which was extremely similar to the samurai that was in
my dreams as a child and what's more is that it somehow relates to her teaching about masks
because the samurai was wearing a mask in my dream as a child and here, so i looked everywhere online
for a picture to best show you what i mean by this samurai so i'll put that on the screen now
this was really the most similar one i could find i don't know anything about samurais
and i couldn't find much about them in terms of spirituality so if any of you have any knowledge
or wisdom about the spiritual significance of samurais i'd be really grateful if you could share
that with me in the comments below too, but yeah while watching this priestess i think i realized
that perhaps this samurai wasn't actually a bad thing it was perhaps a sign in the future that
i would take an interest in astral projection and the ego and things like that maybe i don't know
you know i'm very much into the idea of us taking a spiritual warrior kind of attitude and approach
towards astral projection because you need courage and willpower to do these sorts of practices to
go into the astral to overcome yourself overcome your fears and desires so perhaps it's related to
that i'm not sure so yeah i was pretty speechless at this point i didn't know what to make of what
was happening and everyone else in the room was even more silent now too, nonetheless i liked her
style of teaching she didn't just talk, and say words, she knew these people were not self-aware
and so she did activities with them and showed them things in order to make impressions on their
subconscious in hopes that it would, or should, affect their consciousness overall in some way
so after she did this shapeshifting display someone knew came through
the big doorway that i had entered through too and i was very surprised to see someone i knew
and it was one of the least people i expected to be in a place like this, i didn't know her that
well she was more of an acquaintance, an old colleague at a place i used to work at, uh so
she came into the temple with this gleaming smile and happiness on her face that i had
actually never seen before in the physical, keep in mind i worked with her for about three years...
she started clapping her hands and shouting saying wow this is amazing thank you i'm
so excited to be here, everyone responded cheering for her clearly happy for her too
this is a woman in her 60s, i think, who barely expressed herself like this in the physical she's
usually very dreary and sad you know i often felt sorry for her because there was always something
she was upset about or involved with some drama and also the other colleagues were a bit mean to
her people gossiped about her stuff like that so yeah i was happy to see her like this too
but i was more surprised if anything, so as she's shouting celebrating with happiness the priestess
walks over to her puts her arm around her shoulder and calms her down and she says, "yes yes
but you must wait the path isn't easy, we first have to accept our suffering before going forward,
you have to accept and work through your suffering!" i couldn't have thought of anything better to say
to this woman who i knew had been going through a lot of suffering herself and had a hard time
dealing with it... and with that i woke up and of course i quickly wrote down the entire experience,
a big thing i got from this experience was that the way we're influenced at night is not so much
by intellectual ideas or conversations but ultimately through our feelings
things that can spur on an emotional response is usually more influential, so i can see how these
influential experiences out of the body at night whether conscious or not can have an effect on our
spiritual growth and even perhaps on the decisions that we make when we wake up, you know you often
hear of people just 'waking up one day' and making a spontaneous decision, or coming to a realization,
that perhaps they finally want to do what they've been wanting to do for a while or perhaps they
realize they want to end a certain relationship or change their job or move countries etc, we're
not conscious of it but i suspect that we can be heavily influenced while we're asleep, this is just
one reason why astral projection is a great thing to practice you know some people ask me "is astral
projection dangerous? can someone take over your body? maybe i shouldn't do it"... and i'm like well
you leave the body every night anyway wouldn't you rather know what you're up to than not at all?
wouldn't it be safer to be conscious of your experience at night? so that you can understand the
possible influences and what your consciousness-activity is up to while you're asleep?
do you sometimes wake up with moods or you wake up extremely happy and you don't know why?
wouldn't you like to know why? we all dream every night but we're just not aware of them... all right well
if you enjoyed this video and would like to hear more experiences like this please leave a like,
subscribe, click the bell button so you know when i upload a new video, and if you'd like to support
the channel there's a link for the patreon in the description below, thank you for listening
and stay conscious and lucid as you might just find yourself in a classroom of your own one day
